CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 11, 1957, pg. 15 reads: "Young Fry Step Out in Colorful Fashion Show! - Charlene Wilson, Willie Thomas - Portions of accompanying article reads: "Some of Pittsburgh's most delightful younger set members set a fast pace of fashions at the A. Leo Weil School Friday night, when the Centre Avenue Community Club presented a happy revue, complete with a singing, dancing prelude to styles..."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Charlene Wilson wearing plaid dress and Willie Thomas wearing trench coat and fedora, standing on stage in A. Leo Weil school for Community Club sponsored Fashion Show
